Title: Asset Pricing with Conditioning Information: A New Test 
Abstract:
 This paper presents a new test of conditional versions of the
 Sharpe-Lintner CAPM, the Jagannathan and Wang (1996) extension of the
 CAPM, and the Fama and French (1993) three-factor model. The test is based
 on a general nonparametric methodology that avoids functional form
 misspecification of betas, risk premia, and the stochastic discount
 factor. Our results provide a novel view of empirical performance of these
 models. In particular, we find that a nonparametric version of the Fama
 and French model performs well, even when challenged by momentum
 portfolios. Copyright 2003 by the American Finance Association. 
