Title: A Monte Carlo Method for Optimal Portfolios 
Abstract:
 This paper proposes a new simulation-based approach for optimal portfolio
 allocation in realistic environments with complex dynamics for the state
 variables and large numbers of factors and assets. A first illustration
 involves a choice between equity and cash with nonlinear interest rate and
 market price of risk dynamics. Intertemporal hedging demands significantly
 increase the demand for stocks and exhibit low volatility. We then analyze
 settings where stock returns are also predicted by dividend yields and
 where investors have wealth-dependent relative risk aversion. Large-scale
 problems with many assets, including the Nasdaq, SP500, bonds, and cash,
 are also examined. Copyright 2003 by the American Finance Association. 
